## Product (Domain Entity) 
The Product is responsible for maintaining its identity through its name, category, and lifespan while holding a list of one or more materials. It exposes its composition details to collaborators like RecyclingGuidance and ImpactCalculationStrategy for system-wide analysis. It acts as the central entity that coordinates with external strategies to determine its environmental footprint.

## Material (Domain Entity) 
The Material represents a physical substance defined by its name, impact values, and specific recycling instructions. It is designed to be a reusable entity across multiple products, ensuring that environmental data remains consistent throughout the system. It collaborates with MaterialComposition to define how it is utilized within a specific product context.

## ImpactCalculationStrategy (Strategy Role) 
This role defines an interchangeable metric for calculating environmental impact based on a product's specific materials and composition. It computes a final result by reading values from materials and product services, allowing for different environmental metrics to be swapped easily. It ensures the calculation logic remains independent of the Product entity's core data.

## RecyclingGuidance (Domain Service) 
This service is responsible for deriving end-of-life guidance by combining the rules and instructions of all materials within a product. It specifically handles edge cases for mixed-material products to ensure the user receives clear, safe recycling advice. It takes a Product as input and analyzes the MaterialComposition to produce its output.


## RecyclingCategory (Value Object/Enum) 
The RecyclingCategory classifies materials into stable, reusable types and carries the necessary recycling labels for the system. It is owned by both materials and products to ensure that recycling types remain consistent across the entire domain. It provides the classification framework that RecyclingGuidance uses to sort and group disposal rules.
